headline.main: LONG-ISLAND; Mortality in Brooklyn. New-Year's Day in Brooklyn.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Health Officer reports 68 deaths for the week ending the 27th inst., from the following diseases: Apoplexy, cancer, dropsy, do. in the chest, congestive fever, puerperal do., remittent do., heart disease, hemorrhage of the lungs, inflammation of the brain, do. kidney, do. liver, premature birth, 1 each;

docs.lead_paragraph: Steamship George Law, Commander W. L. HERNDON, U.S.N., left Aspinwall at 9 1/2 o'clock on the evening of the 1965 inst., and arrived at Quarantine at 8 o'clock on the afternoon of the 28th, having expertenced heavy weather and strong N. W. winds since passing the latitude of Charleston.
